description.5: Human sacrifices, mass suicides, and more! Johnny Blaze is working with a local senator to shut down a death cult, but will it be enough?
description.6: Hulk and the Goldbug go head-to-head with Tyrannus! Will our hero and his ally be defeated once more, failing the people of El Dorado?
description.7: Using SHIELD's controlling interest in Stark Enterprises, Nick Fury attempts to manufacture a cornucopia of weaponry.
description.8: Jessica Drew: Bounty hunter! Trying a career switch-up, Spider-Woman finds a new partner in Scotty McDowell and targets some fresh hits.
description.10: What if Doctor Strange became the devil's disciple instead of Sorcerer Supreme? Uatu the Watcher answers this question, as Stephen Strange discovers it's far easier to be bad, than good. The Ancient One teaches Dormammu's assistant a lesson he won't soon forget!
description.11: Reed and Ben's powers are nearly gone from the effects of the Skrull's ageing ray. Does this mean Earth is helpless against Galactus?
description.12: Spider-Man must enter the hive in order to defeat Swarm!
description.15: Ben continues to dig into Matt's past. Daredevil takes on Bullseye and Slaughter's gang in order to rescue the Black Widow.
description.16: Tyrannus rises from the life force of the Hulk! Do Hulk and the Goldbug stand a chance?
description.17: One of the most memorable and powerful Iron Man stories deserves a cover worthy of its stature. Thankfully, Bob Layton delivers, providing a cover that stands tall to this day.
description.19: Sphinx vs. Terrax and Galactus! Meanwhile, an uninvited guest lurks around the Baxter Building while the team is held in Egypt!
description.20: Swarm lives! Is a swarm of killer bees too much for Spider-Man?
description.22: Spider-Man has been brutally beaten by Kingpin, and is too weak to lick his wounds. After a stint at a hospital, (where he remains masked), Spider-Man continues to convalesce at the Restwell Retirement Home. Another problem on top of broken bones? Restwell's Chief of Medicine is none other than Mysterio! Spider-Man falls victim to mind games, while J. Jonah Jameson loses his mind.
description.23: Is this the end of the Avengers!? After Iron Man tells Peter Gyrich that the Avengers will not force super-powered beings to join their team, the cantankerous Gyrich threatens to end the Avengers program once-and-for-all!
description.24: It's a battle to the death as Captain America face off with the Widowmaker! Will Captain America survive what comes next? Or will the Widowmaker and his partner in crime, Stephen Tuval outwit the Super-Soldier?
description.25: Still coming out of his comatose state, Wundarr unwittingly frees Solarr from his containment!
description.27: Moondragon leaves the team of heroes on bad terms when James-Michael Starling makes a bold decision to keep his friends safe.
description.28: Darth Vader is on the warpath to find the name of the person who destroyed the Death Star...and no one will stand in his way.
description.37: Inside the Project Pegasus facility, Thing, Quasar, and Giant-Man take on a fighting-female fire squad!
description.40: As the Defenders work to find Omega, Ruby Thursday and Dibbuk steal his body from the morgue...all while being attacked by Protar aliens!
description.41: Johnny Blaze saves an innocent woman being sacrificed by a death cult, but all might not be as it seems!
description.42: Hulk and the Goldbug enter the secret, golden city of El Dorado! Meanwhile, Bruce is attacked in an attempt to save Jarella.
description.46: Imagine if the tables were turned- if Spider-Woman, Ghost Rider, and Captain Mar-Vell...were hard bitten villains! As Arachne, Jessica Drew lives her life on the lam from S.H.I.E.L.D.! Captain Mar-Vell declares war against Earthlings, while Johnny Blaze's powers lead him to murder!
description.47: Galactus finds a new herald in Tyros. Terrax the Tamer the born!
description.48: Manipulated by Mindworm! Mindworm uses Peter as a pawn and invades his dreams.
description.50: Jabba the Hut is looking to get his payment from Han and Chewie, through deadly force if necessary.
description.53: Collecting such tales as the Fowl of Fear, The $64,000 Desperado, From Hell It Cometh…and Chair-Thing! Check out the maladjusted mallard in his monthly mag!
description.59: The return of Kingpin! Wilson Fisk seemingly drowned in his last battle with Spider-Man. But this super-sized crime lord is scrappier than we thought! Kingpin will stop at nothing to reclaim his hold over New York's crime syndicate, and Spider-Man may be powerless to stop him! Guest-starring Vanessa Fisk, desperate to save the man she loves.
description.60: After his near heart-attack in Wundagore, the Avengers deliver Quicksilver to his Inhuman wife on Attilan. There, Pietro finds out that he and Crystal are expecting a baby! Concerned about her own legacy, the Scarlet Witch considers motherhood, and whether it is possible to have a child with Vision.
description.61: It's a modern day fairytale as Captain America travels to the top of the world, to rescue a damsel in distress. But Cap will learn soon that this is no ordinary damsel! Plus: beware the Hawk Riders!
description.65: While Thing tries to capture Nuklo with the rest of the team at Project Pegasus, Thundra is bested by a mysterious new fighter during a wrestling match!
description.67: Valkyrie and Hellcat are stalled in battle when the Foolkiller takes Dollar Bill as a prisoner!
description.68: Bullseye captures Black Widow in order to flush Daredevil out.
description.69: The Goldbug pulls the wool over Hulk's eyes! And by the time the Green Goliath realizes he's been tricked...it's already too late!
description.70: Jessica Drew's disco date transforms into a melted, waxy monstrosity!
description.72: Reed makes a deal with Galactus allowing him to devour Earth. What kind of deal is that?!
description.73: The fight continues! Lizard and Iguana fight for supremacy of the lizard world.
description.75: Peter Parker is left reeling in the wake of Aunt May's death. How did this happen? And why? Plus, Peter quits his job at the Bugle when he's had enough of Jameson's harmful bias toward Spider-Man. What will the future hold for the web-slinger when all seems lost?
description.76: Modred, dark sorcerer of Wundagore, and the possessed Scarlet Witch, attack the Avengers as they crash-land in Transia. The Witch of Wundagore holds her teammates captive, but her dark magic is no match for her mighty teammates!
description.77: After learning the tragic fate of Sharon Carter, Captain America turns away from the life of heroics. But before he is anything else, he is a soldier, and when Nick Fury asks for his help on a special mission, Captain America's accepts proudly!
description.81: Luke is in danger and the only one who can save him is....C3PO?
description.84: When a Bodavian diplomat is murdered by the Silencer, the Falcon thinks he knows who's behind the mask.
description.85: In Omaha, Johnny Blaze comes across a group attempting to beat his car-jumping record, but their ties to the mob might force Ghost Rider to jump into action before it’s too late!
description.86: The President and Clay Quartermain watch in horror as Hulk rampages through Central City, California. An alien threat enables a plan against Hulk.
description.87: Jessica Drew loses her spider-suit while on a night out on the town! Spider-Woman's pheromone powers are tested.
description.89: Is this it? Is this...the END of Dracula?
description.91: Arcade has brainwashed Colossus and he may very well be the most dangerous part of Murderworld for the X-Men.
description.92: Empress R'Klll declares herself leader of the Skrulls! The Skrulls prepare for a final assault! Meanwhile, the FF discovers an incredible graveyard...
description.93: Spider-Man must try and fight both Lizard and Iguana to save the Connors family.
description.98: As Ben Grimm wanders the halls of Project Pegasus, he is attacked by the Nth Command's agent, Deathlok. When Thing tries to reason with Luther Manning, the cyborg reveals that he no longer possesses an organic mind and is all A.I programming!

0.text: A group of mysterious (and self-righteous) beings attack Machine Man after witnessing our hero avenge a violent crime.

1.text: Fu Manchu gathers his greatest resources to plot his return.

9.text: After meeting a man name El Vampiro, Thor receives a strange message about a dangerous foe he must do battle with. His name is El Toro Rojo and his one goal is to gore the Thunder God!

13.text: Spider-Woman finally comes face-to-face with Spider-Man while Peter Parker is working on location in Los Angeles!

14.text: In a bid to escape Muir Island, Proteus is moving from body to body, all the while pitting the X-Men against one another. What will it take to stop this Omega-level mutant? If it means taking Proteus out for good, are the X-Men willing to go that far?

17.text: DEMON IN A BOTTLE PART 9 Tony Stark has been ravaged by scandal, his life brought to its lowest point by addiction...can anyone set him straight!
One of the most memorable and powerful Iron Man stories deserves a cover worthy of its stature. Thankfully, Bob Layton delivers, providing a cover that stands tall to this day.

18.text: Thor battles the Destroyer in Asgard! Guest-starring Ares, Athena, Hercules and Zeus!

29.text: Captain Marvel is hit with two life-changing discoveries- he's in love with Elysius…and he's the destined protector of Earth and all its creatures!

30.text: Man-Thing’s mysterious transformation from Ted Sallis into Marvel’s swamp monster is recounted here!

31.text: Shang-Chi's evil father, Fu Manchu, abducts Sir Denis!

34.text: DEMON IN A BOTTLE PART 8 Seeking to prove his innocence, Tony Stark confronts Justin Hammer. But instead of a chit-chat, Iron Man encounters a dozen super-powered villains ready for a showdown!

35.text: The X-Men-in response to Lorna's call for help-are en route to Muir Island. What will they find there? And what happens when they learn that Mutant X has escaped?!

36.text: The Amazing Spider-Man partners up with the Guardians of the Galaxy and takes on the devilish duo of Hammer and Anvil!

39.text: Strange enters the statue of the Black Knight, as Clea begrudgingly cares for Victoria. When Stephen doubts his abilities as Sorcerer Supreme, the Dweller of Darkness claims his victory!

44.text: The Enforcer unloads his rage against Spider-Woman and the Werewolf by Night!

45.text: Thor does battle with Hero in defense of the Celestials. If the Odinson fails, the Celestials will meet the darkest of fates!

51.text: Tyndall has reached the heart of Weirdworld’s mystery, yet there is much still to be revealed. The stand against evil culminates in the Soul Shrine, climactic ending to the Warriors of the Shadow Realm arc. What is the floating island of Klarn? Why do Tyndall and Velanna have no memory of a life there? And what is the shattering secret behind the Darklens Gems?

52.text: The Heroes for Hire get some backlash from the press when they are linked with J.P. Preston in the Bugle! Iron Fist and Misty Knight run into an old, suspicious friend, and the Big Apple Bomber wreaks havoc in the city!

53.text: Collecting such tales as the Fowl of Fear, The $64,000 Desperado, From Hell It Cometh…and Chair-Thing! Check out the maladjusted mallard in his monthly mag!

54.text: Peter Spaulding hopes to find Machine Man gainful employment…but the two run afoul of the Binary Bug instead! In his role as an insurance investigator, will MM save Delmar Insurance from a corporate thief?

55.text: The leopard cultists get the better of Shang-Chi and his friends!

62.text: DEMON IN A BOTTLE PART 7 The mastermind behind the failing Iron Man armor is finally revealed!

63.text: Jean Grey is alive and well on Muir Island. When Cyclops learns the news of this, he also discovers that the security on Muir Island has been breached and that Lorna is in grave danger! How will the X-Men respond?

64.text: The Invaders barely survived their last encounter with Baron Blood. What will they do now that the Nazi vampire has returned?

66.text: Shang-Chi joins the fray alongside Spider-Man, Nick Fury and Black Widow! The Silver Samurai doesn't stand a chance!

71.text: Sif versus Storm Giants! The Warriors Three versus Fafnir The Dragon! The Forgotten One versus the Celestials! Three epic, divine showdowns that cannot be missed!

78.text: Shang-Chi must fight Fu Manchu's leopard cult of assassins, although his father turns out not to be dead after all!

82.text: Captain Marvel is trapped inside a living computer! And trying to escape ISAAC's clutches proves a cerebral nightmare!

83.text: DEMON IN A BOTTLE PART 6 As Tony continues to lose control over his armor and his life, a terrible accident occurs! Can Stark make it out of this unscathed?

84.text: When a Bodavian diplomat is murdered by the Silencer, the Falcon thinks he knows who's behind the mask.

88.text: When Odin denies Thor the aid he needs in a fight against deviants, the Thunder God is captured. With no backup in sight, Sersi makes a daring rescue attempt!

90.text: What if Shang-Chi, the Master of Kung Fu, had remained loyal to his evil father, Fu Manchu?!

95.text: The Master of Kung Fu must fight the drugs in his system in order to win his ongoing battle with Zaran.

99.text: Spidey is joined by the Master of Kung Fu himself, Shang-Chi!
